The CAAM's Job descriptor language is very powerful and feature-rich.
However, as far as I know, the TamaGo driver does not implement the entire job descriptor language and cannot use features such as black keys.

**Proposal**: Export the `job` function found in the [CAAM driver](https://github.com/usbarmory/tamago/blob/master/soc/nxp/caam/job.go) so that developers can send custom jobs to the CAAM:

```go
func (hw *CAAM) Job(hdr *Header, jd []byte) (err error) {
	once.Do(hw.initJobRing)
	return hw.jr.add(hdr, jd)
}
```

